******
[1] Nakuru
Date: 8 Apr 2019
Source: Standard Media [edited]
https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/article/2001320169/vaccination-of-rhinos-begins-after-anthrax-reports


Vaccination of southern white rhinos at Lake Nakuru National Park has started following an anthrax outbreak that has killed 10 buffaloes.

The Kenya Wildlife Service (KWS) yesterday [7 Apr 2019] confirmed that the dead buffaloes tested positive for anthrax. Four more buffalo carcasses were found after the dead 10.

Susan Koech, the Principal Secretary for wildlife, said the 4 carcasses were found by KWS patrolling teams, although it has not been confirmed that they died of anthrax.

While commenting on the rhino vaccinations, Dr Koech said: "Currently, 14 of the 15 white rhinos have been vaccinated and so have 4 of the 63 black rhinos."

[Byline: Caroline Chebet]

